# Conclusion
# wifi (WPA2-Enterprise / eduroam) via wpa_supplicant.conf – not working
# iPhone hotspot – not working
# USB-C direct connect via config.txt/cmdline.txt – not working
# HDMI keyboard/monitor setup – not available
# solution: reset, assign static IP, use reliable Ethernet cable

# Find the Pi or laptop IP
arp -a

# Stress test the link
ping -D -s 1400 169.233.255.254

# Watch link up/down events
dmesg -w | egrep -i 'eth0: Link is (Up|Down)'

# Windows ICS (Internet Connection Sharing)
Win+R → ncpa.cpl
Right-click Wi-Fi adapter → Properties
Sharing tab:
  [✓] Allow other network users to connect
  Select: Ethernet
OK
Ethernet becomes: 192.168.137.1

# Configure Static IP on Raspberry Pi (Headless)

1. Insert SD card into laptop
2. Open boot partition
3. Edit: cmdline.txt
4. One line only — add to the end:

ip=192.168.137.5::192.168.137.1:255.255.255.0

# Example final:
console=serial0,115200 console=tty1 root=...rootwait quiet splash \
ip=192.168.137.5::192.168.137.1:255.255.255.0

# Reset SSH hostname entry after reinstall
ssh-keygen -R raspberrypi.local
